main event: A star-like object was observed traveling east and disappearing 40 degrees above the southeast horizon in Long Beach, California on September 27, 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a star, traveling east.
The object started from a point on the horizon and disappeared 40 degrees above the southeast horizon.
The sighting was reported to the 5SD Command on September 28, 1963.
The weather conditions were clear with 15-18 miles of visibility.
photographs: No photographs were included in the report.
